    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ancient manuscripts generally taking the form of the modern book: bound leaves of paper or parchment with information inscribed on both faces, attached at a center fold. For books that are printed rather than inscribed, before 1501, use 'incunabula.'</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
